Originally Answered: Which cruise company do you recommend for someone who has never been on a cruise before?

I would recommend booking a cruise according to your interests and energy level. Lets start with bargain cruises for those who just want to get away to a beach and party. Carnival has the corner on that market with Norwegian Cruises close behind.

If youre looking for the next price point, Princess would be my recommendation.

For those who enjoy elaborate theme parties, a wider variety of meal-choices and are traveling with families, definitely Royal Caribbean!! They are non-stop fun and yet, they keep it classy!

Holland America. Almost luxurious at a reasonable price, the closest cruise line now that most resembles the old Renaissance Line, which was very high class (country club casual, Ren called it) at a worth-it price.

Unless you are traveling with your kids, do NOT go on a Disney cruise. It is just too noisy and kid-oriented.

And, unless you want a fraternity/sorority type cruise, do NOT go on Carnival. Way too much drinking and partying.

I am biased to a degree but here goes;

-for families, teenagers, fun seekers, Carnival, NCL, and Royal

Originally Answered: Which cruise company do you recommend for someone who has never been on a cruise before?

I would say which ever cruise lines operated out of your favorite cruise port. You may have a cruise port in your area. You dont have to pay for parking while you are cruising. You can just take a taxi or ask a friend to drop you off at the port.

In that case there may not be a lot of choices. There may be only one cruise line or maybe only one cruise ship operating out of that port. Hop on it. Some people love cruises some dont. It is my favorite way to travel.

Our first and most fun cruise was on Royal Caribbean about 30 years ago. Since then we have cruised on Princess, Holland America, Crystal and Azamara. By far, Crystal and Azamara are our favorites mostly because they have under 1,000 passengers. We are not fond of those mega-ships with over 3,000 passengers and a theme park onboard. We go to relax, enjoy fine dining, and explore the various ports.

Originally Answered: Which cruise company do you recommend for someone who has never been on a cruise before?

I recommend you dont start with selecting a cruise line; you start with selecting a travel agent. Look for an agent that specializes in cruises and let them take you through the process of identifying your must haves and like to haves on your cruise. They will ask you questions about things you will never have thought about. Then using your criteria they can help you select the best option for your first adventure. After your first cruise and your experience with the myriad of things that go into selecting the best line youll be able to make an informed decision for yourself.

What led you to work on a cruise ship?

A teacher, I had summers off. I took a gig as a musician on two cruises, I play the trumpet and guitar. They pay union scale, not big bucks, but you do get a free cruise. The 8 piece orchestra played 8 hours a day, 6 until 2, six days a week, unless some of the passengers wanted music earlier, later, or on our day off (Wednesday, I think). If that was the case, they had to cut a deal with the orchestra leader. He was fair with them, and us. Hed hand out the cash the next day. There was always a star, a vocalist.
